        <num>CC 1312</num>
        <heading>1312.  Partition suits by tutors and curators</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1312.  Partition suits by tutors and curators.
Tutors of minors, and curators of persons interdicted have the right to institute in their names suits for the partition of the effects of successions, whether movable or immovable, falling to minors or persons interdicted, provided they are specially authorized by the judge on the advice of the family meeting.</p>
        </content>
